    "body": "Exactly right approach \n\nSent from Outlook Mobile. Yes, it works with gmail.\n\nOn Fri, Apr 8, 2016 at 12:54 PM -0700, \"Andy Schwartzmeyer\" notifications@github.com wrote:\n\nThe solution (for now) is to just remove the man alias, such that help opens PowerShell's help and man opens the Linux manual. This is exactly how Bash works as well.\n\nWhile we can certainly fix the Get-Help cmdlet to fall-through and search the man pages, I consider this future work.\n\n—\nYou are receiving this because you authored the thread.\nReply to this email directly or view it on GitHub\n",
